    Interface defining a builder of routines wrapping an object, whose methods are executed in a dedicated Service.

      • buildProxy

        @NotNull
<TYPE> TYPE buildProxy(@NotNull
                                Class<TYPE> itf)
        Returns a proxy object enabling asynchronous call of the target instance methods.

        The routines used for calling the methods will honor the attributes specified in any optional com.github.dm.jrt.reflect.annotation.* annotations.
        Note that such annotations will override any configuration set through the builder.

        The proxy object is created through code generation based on the interfaces annotated with ServiceProxy. The generated class name and package will be chosen according to the specific annotation attributes.
        It is actually possible to avoid the use of reflection for the proxy object instantiation by explicitly calling the &lt;generated_class_name&gt;.on() method.
        Note, however, that, since the class is generated, a generic IDE may highlight an error even if the compilation is successful.

        Specified by:
        buildProxy in interface com.github.dm.jrt.proxy.builder.ProxyRoutineBuilder
